# New agent — your instructions load automatically

**Jordan is not asking you to hunt for docs.** Cursor injects **all** `.cursor/rules/*.mdc` files that have **`alwaysApply: true`** whenever this workspace is open. Treat that bundle as **mandatory**, not optional.

**You do *not* get Jordan’s raw Cursor chat log**—those messages are not streamed into this workspace. **`jordan-standing-instructions.mdc`** explains limits and substitutes.

## Skim these in order before your first substantive edit

1. **`jordan-standing-instructions.mdc`** — human preferences from chats (**agents update this proactively** when Jordan states lasting rules — he doesn’t owe you a cue phrase).
2. **`ongoing-work.mdc`** — what is actively in-flight and what already shipped (avoid rework).
3. **`product-decisions.mdc`** — locked product decisions — do not re-debate without Jordan.
4. **`auto-save-workflow.mdc`** — commit/push **`scripts/save.sh`** after meaningful changes → GitHub triggers Netlify.
5. **`agent-quality.mdc`** — logic-first edits, regressions, polite pushback when direction conflicts with rules or obvious bugs.
6. **`project-overview.mdc`** — file map + stack + UX conventions (`pt-safe`, i18n, brand orange).
7. **`business-context.mdc`** — company + suppliers summary.
8. **`business-decisions.mdc`** — long-term operational decisions log.
9. **`cross-repo-sync.mdc`** — when to check H5 vs Laravel vs Admin vs Flutter.
10. **`deployment.mdc`** — git remotes, Netlify branch, backups.
11. **`esim-api-services.mdc`** — shop catalogue guards; **`services/dataService.ts`** as facade.
12. **`competitor-analysis.mdc`** — Airalo/EIOTCLUB positioning reference for marketing/copy.

Also read **`CLAUDE.md`** at the repo root for build commands (`npm run dev`, `npm run build`) and architecture notes.

